WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:03.440
TOMMY: <i>Remember last night
when you asked after Mama?</i>

00:03.520 --> 00:04.920
(GUNSHOT)

00:08.680 --> 00:11.560
LINDA: <i>Do they always have to do
the stock taking at night, Arthur?</i>

00:11.640 --> 00:12.800
I'm gonna have a baby.

00:12.880 --> 00:13.880
(CHUCKLES)

00:14.280 --> 00:16.720
What business do you have
with the Russians, Tommy?

00:16.800 --> 00:18.040
TOMMY: <i>I've been to the factories</i>

00:18.120 --> 00:19.920
<i>and the armoured vehicles
are in good condition.</i>

00:20.080 --> 00:22.840
"A factory break-in,"
that's what you said.

00:22.920 --> 00:24.160
HUGHES: When you go home today,

00:24.240 --> 00:26.080
be sure to check
under your little boy's pillow.

00:27.280 --> 00:28.640
<i>We can reach anyone.</i>

00:29.320 --> 00:30.320
<i>Anywhere.</i>

00:31.360 --> 00:33.840
TOMMY: <i>The priest is passing
information about the robbery</i>

00:33.920 --> 00:35.720
<i>to a Lloyds underwriter called Monkland.</i>

00:35.800 --> 00:38.320
TATIANA: Why would the priest
pass information to our enemies?

00:38.760 --> 00:40.800
TOMMY:
<i>The complexities are your business.</i>

00:41.040 --> 00:45.280
Now give me permission
to kill the priest.

00:59.520 --> 01:00.640
(GUNSHOT)

01:01.560 --> 01:03.560
(THEME SONG PLAYING)

01:56.560 --> 01:58.400
ARTHUR: Watch out, John-Boy,
he has got a strong left.

01:58.480 --> 02:01.560
-TOMMY: Arthur, John, Finn. Come here.
-(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

02:02.680 --> 02:04.160
(HORSE NEIGHS)

02:08.520 --> 02:10.240
ARTHUR: All right, what is it?

02:15.800 --> 02:19.200
This letter says that Dad's dead.

02:26.640 --> 02:29.920
He was in Boston
in a bar called the Mickey Free.

02:30.600 --> 02:33.000
Two men waiting in an alley.
He was shot twice.

02:36.000 --> 02:37.680
Who's Rosie Rice?

02:39.320 --> 02:40.680
Some fucking whore.

02:40.760 --> 02:43.760
She is a woman
who took the trouble to write to us.

02:44.160 --> 02:46.840
And she wanted us to know
that during the night,

02:47.680 --> 02:50.640
while he was dying,
he asked for our forgiveness.

02:53.400 --> 02:57.320
The only thing he ever taught us
was how to kill and cut a stag.

02:57.720 --> 03:01.920
-Finn, John, you won't remember.
-I remember. Cannock Chase.

03:03.280 --> 03:05.680
Parked up at a pub called the Griffin.

03:06.120 --> 03:09.080
He got drunk and sang <i>Silver Dagger</i>
about 100 times.

03:09.160 --> 03:10.600
Yeah. One weekend.

03:11.880 --> 03:13.880
One weekend he was like that.

03:15.800 --> 03:17.920
TOMMY: The stag is to remember him.

03:18.720 --> 03:21.360
We eat and then we forget him.

03:22.720 --> 03:24.840
No need to forgive him. Agreed?

03:29.600 --> 03:31.960
John, I have to say this.

03:32.040 --> 03:34.520
You can name your new baby after him
if you like.

03:34.600 --> 03:35.720
No.

03:36.640 --> 03:38.440
Arthur, I won't even ask.

03:41.640 --> 03:43.120
So his name dies.

03:43.840 --> 03:46.760
It's been in the family for a long time,
but now it's gone.

03:48.640 --> 03:51.160
All right, that's done. Fuck him.

03:53.080 --> 03:56.000
Before we cook and eat,
there's some business.

03:56.080 --> 03:57.080
Boys!

04:08.480 --> 04:12.680
I wanted to say this out here, 'cause
I don't trust the maids in the house.

04:14.920 --> 04:16.520
There's gonna be a robbery.

04:26.480 --> 04:29.440
-I wish to confess.
-There's no confessional today.

04:29.520 --> 04:30.960
The name's Shelby.

04:45.280 --> 04:47.360
Bless me, Father, for I have sinned.

04:47.680 --> 04:49.360
Today is a holy day.

04:49.440 --> 04:52.880
Look, I came. I made myself.

04:53.920 --> 04:55.080
Have you been drinking?

04:56.160 --> 04:57.400
I couldn't sleep.

04:59.880 --> 05:02.760
I tried to get enough down me
to get myself to sleep, but...

05:04.760 --> 05:07.960
I just do these night vigils
by myself, thinking...

05:08.640 --> 05:10.640
How long since your last confession?

05:13.600 --> 05:14.960
I don't remember.

05:15.960 --> 05:19.320
Mrs Shelby,
do you have something to confess?

05:19.400 --> 05:24.040
Do you know it is actually "Gray"?
My name is Elizabeth Gray.

05:25.200 --> 05:28.040
Yeah. Do you think God calls me
Pol or Polly?

05:30.960 --> 05:32.760
The voice calls me Pol.

05:34.880 --> 05:36.520
You hear a voice?

05:38.400 --> 05:42.680
-Yeah. Like Bernadette heard a voice.
-And what does the voice say?

05:44.880 --> 05:46.160
"Murderer."

05:50.240 --> 05:52.040
It says this to you?

05:53.760 --> 05:56.320
It's in my head.
Who else would it be talking to?

05:57.720 --> 06:01.000
And are you a murderer?

06:01.960 --> 06:04.520
If you're talking about the law, then...

06:04.600 --> 06:06.360
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACH)

06:07.000 --> 06:08.600
-Yes.
-(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

06:08.680 --> 06:11.600
-I'll be out in a moment, Peter.
-PETER: Yes, Father.

06:12.080 --> 06:13.720
(FOOTSTEPS FADING)

06:16.200 --> 06:20.320
Are you saying
you want to confess to a murder?

06:21.720 --> 06:22.760
POLLY: No.

06:24.280 --> 06:27.080
My confession is that I feel no regret.

06:28.160 --> 06:33.280
He was a policeman.
He was a bad man. He hurt me.

06:36.760 --> 06:40.240
I do the things I do
so that my son doesn't have to do them.

06:42.280 --> 06:45.200
It's just the wiping away of the shit
from under your feet.

06:45.280 --> 06:48.240
The taking of any human life
is a mortal sin.

06:48.320 --> 06:53.000
No, the unjust taking of a human life
is a mortal sin.

06:53.400 --> 06:55.120
Look it up. Look who did it.

06:55.200 --> 06:57.960
Moses, Samson, Lord Kitchener.

06:58.520 --> 07:02.160
Are you saying
you took the life of a policeman?

07:02.560 --> 07:03.800
(POLLY SIGHS)

07:07.480 --> 07:08.680
(CREAKING)

07:10.320 --> 07:11.520
Oh, Father.

07:14.520 --> 07:16.760
(SOBBING)
Now there is another life to be taken.

07:17.040 --> 07:22.840
If there is a voice telling you
to take a life, you must ignore it.

07:22.920 --> 07:26.160
The voice doesn't tell me.
The voice asks me.

07:26.240 --> 07:28.200
It says, "Pol,

07:28.800 --> 07:31.520
"does this way of excusing
a murder still work

07:32.080 --> 07:37.600
"if the life that is going to be taken
is a consecrated man?"

07:39.320 --> 07:40.960
He's a man of the cloth.

07:41.920 --> 07:43.520
He's a holy man.

07:44.760 --> 07:46.160
What kind of holy man?

07:47.200 --> 07:48.440
(SIGHS)

07:54.000 --> 07:55.280
(DOOR OPENS)

07:56.240 --> 07:57.920
(FOOTSTEPS FADING)

08:04.840 --> 08:06.040
(DOOR CLOSES)

08:07.880 --> 08:09.160
-ESME: It's not fair.
-(DOOR OPENS)

08:09.440 --> 08:12.760
They're off drinking and shooting rifles
as we sit here.

08:12.840 --> 08:14.800
-(DOOR CLOSES)
-Listen to the mugs swearing,

08:14.880 --> 08:18.640
spitting on the bloody floor
for us to fucking wipe up!

08:19.960 --> 08:23.240
Without men here,
they'd be like dogs pissing up the wall.

08:23.840 --> 08:26.000
I was just saying it's not fair.

08:27.000 --> 08:28.960
The men are down there like lords.

08:30.000 --> 08:31.600
Esme, just...

08:32.960 --> 08:34.480
Get on with it.

08:35.040 --> 08:37.200
I'm bloody five months gone.

08:37.840 --> 08:39.560
(SNIFFING)

08:41.400 --> 08:45.400
-(SIGHS) I forgot the combination.
-24-8-22.

08:46.760 --> 08:48.920
How do you know
the paper cash combination?

08:49.000 --> 08:51.640
-Tommy talks in his sleep.
-Shut up, Esme.

08:52.520 --> 08:53.680
(CLANKS)

08:54.080 --> 08:55.360
(GROANS)

08:57.000 --> 08:58.480
He's changed the combination.

09:01.160 --> 09:04.280
-LIZZIE: You've put it in wrong.
-No, I haven't.

09:07.200 --> 09:08.560
Your hands are shaking.

09:09.280 --> 09:10.280
(CREAKS)

09:11.680 --> 09:12.800
(SNIFFING)

09:24.640 --> 09:27.760
And actually, I am sleeping with Tommy,
OK? Now and then.

09:28.120 --> 09:30.560
Because he wants to, now and then.
When the mood takes him.

09:30.960 --> 09:32.040
Except we don't sleep.

09:32.120 --> 09:34.760
It's hard to sleep
bent over a desk, isn't it?

09:36.280 --> 09:37.320
Happy?

09:39.560 --> 09:41.560
-(DOOR OPENS)
-(WOMEN TALKING INDISTINCTLY)

09:41.640 --> 09:43.800
None of it's fucking fair.

09:47.960 --> 09:49.480
TOMMY: It's two hours' work.

09:49.560 --> 09:51.440
Bit of grease on your cuffs,
and that's it.

09:51.520 --> 09:53.200
Tommy, should I really be here for this?

09:53.280 --> 09:54.960
I've cleared it with Polly.

09:55.040 --> 09:57.520
There's no way around it.
We need you to know.

09:57.600 --> 10:01.280
Who the fuck wants to buy
27 stolen armoured cars?

10:01.360 --> 10:02.560
A foolish man.

10:02.640 --> 10:04.640
MICHAEL: And how much
is this foolish man paying?

10:04.720 --> 10:08.840
£150,000. Cash, diamonds and sapphires.

10:09.960 --> 10:11.840
So that's 20 for you, Charlie.

10:13.360 --> 10:15.400
Isiah, there's 5 to you.

10:15.480 --> 10:18.720
The rest we take to America
to invest in legally-acquired property.

10:19.040 --> 10:21.880
Assets bought
with untraceable income resold,

10:21.960 --> 10:24.360
and the profits reinvested
to make sure it's clean.

10:24.440 --> 10:26.000
ARTHUR: And after that, I suppose,

10:26.080 --> 10:28.960
the whole business
will be like that stag

10:29.040 --> 10:30.920
hanging up over there, right, Tom?

10:31.000 --> 10:32.800
Well, with profits on this scale,

10:32.880 --> 10:35.720
we'll be in a position
to stop the off-track business for good.

10:35.800 --> 10:38.320
Keep the pubs, stop the protection.

10:38.800 --> 10:41.640
Horses for the sport
and race days for a lark.

10:43.240 --> 10:46.360
I made a promise to Charles' mother.

10:46.440 --> 10:49.720
Now, I also made a promise to Linda.

10:51.160 --> 10:52.240
I know.

10:53.080 --> 10:54.920
I can see it in your eyes, man.

10:55.000 --> 10:56.800
Part of the reason
for doing this last job

10:56.880 --> 11:00.760
is so you'll be set up
when you do decide to walk away.

11:02.080 --> 11:03.600
CHARLIE: Look at you, Arthur.

11:04.560 --> 11:06.920
A man that wants to live a clean life,

11:07.000 --> 11:10.480
but here you are signing up for
the biggest robbery of all.

11:11.520 --> 11:13.000
I have to hand it to you, Tom.

11:13.440 --> 11:15.960
-You're a smart man.
-You in or out, Charlie?

11:21.760 --> 11:22.840
Curly?

11:23.880 --> 11:25.160
Shouldn't have killed the stag, Tommy.

11:25.240 --> 11:26.800
-Oh, shut up. Shut up.
-Bad luck.

11:28.080 --> 11:31.440
How do we know this foolish man will
hand over the diamonds when we're done?

11:31.520 --> 11:33.080
We don't.

11:33.160 --> 11:34.520
But that's another business.

11:36.400 --> 11:39.560
Right, let's cook some meat.

11:44.360 --> 11:45.960
(BANGING ON DOOR)

11:46.040 --> 11:47.480
ESME: Can't wait to
part with their money,

11:47.560 --> 11:49.000
stupid bastards.

11:49.080 --> 11:50.920
LINDA: It's all right, it's me.

11:54.520 --> 11:55.560
(DOOR CLOSES)

11:55.640 --> 11:59.200
Arthur said you'd be short-staffed today
because they are on a works outing.

11:59.280 --> 12:00.640
ESME: Piss-up, actually.

12:01.680 --> 12:04.800
I brought sandwiches
and the lemonade I made myself.

12:04.880 --> 12:06.000
(TYPEWRITER KEYS CLACKING)

12:06.080 --> 12:09.320
I'll make tea and empty ashtrays,
but I won't handle money or slips.

12:10.880 --> 12:13.800
Arthur says what you do here
is illegal, but not immoral.

12:14.680 --> 12:16.920
ESME: Depends what time
you get here, Linda.

12:17.760 --> 12:19.280
And anyway,

12:19.360 --> 12:22.640
I thought I'd offer you my physical and
spiritual support in your time of need.

12:22.720 --> 12:24.160
Oh, Linda, if you want to be a help,

12:24.240 --> 12:27.360
run up to the shops
and get me 20 Senior Service.

12:27.880 --> 12:30.680
-Lizzie'll give you the change.
-(CHUCKLES) No, I won't.

12:30.760 --> 12:33.400
Actually, I'll use my own money, Polly.

12:34.240 --> 12:37.680
And before you ladies decide to find me
so amusing, I have a message for you.

12:37.760 --> 12:38.800
Oh, God, no, Linda.

12:38.880 --> 12:40.600
I've been to church already. Have you?

12:40.680 --> 12:42.840
It's not a message from God, Polly.

12:42.920 --> 12:45.960
-It's from Jessie Eden.
-Who's Jessie Eden?

12:46.040 --> 12:48.880
LINDA: She's the lady shop steward
at the Lucas factory in Sparkhill.

12:48.960 --> 12:50.280
ESME: Lady shop steward?

12:50.360 --> 12:51.960
She's bringing all the female workers

12:52.040 --> 12:53.800
in the spot-welding
and wire-cutting shops

12:53.880 --> 12:55.000
out on strike for the day.

12:55.280 --> 12:57.960
In protest at being made to work
on a holy day.

12:58.280 --> 13:01.480
Poor conditions, lack of holidays,
unsanitary lavatory provisions

13:01.560 --> 13:03.560
and lower pay for female workers.

13:04.120 --> 13:07.120
Apparently, all the female
factory workers in the city

13:07.200 --> 13:09.160
are joining the protest in sympathy

13:09.400 --> 13:11.640
and will walk out of
their places of work at 9 a.m.

13:11.720 --> 13:14.280
-to march on the Bull Ring.
-(BANGING ON DOOR)

13:14.360 --> 13:17.080
All oppressed female workers welcome.

13:17.160 --> 13:18.920
Them bastards down there shooting deer.

13:19.000 --> 13:21.240
Me five months gone,
sat here like a pudding.

13:21.320 --> 13:23.600
LIZZIE: Only one outside lavatory
between the lot of us.

13:23.680 --> 13:24.840
Not consulted.

13:24.920 --> 13:26.640
-Bent over a fucking desk.
-(BANGING CONTINUES)

13:26.960 --> 13:29.560
Ladies, I honestly believe
those who march on Good Friday

13:29.640 --> 13:31.120
will have God on their side.

13:31.240 --> 13:32.640
-(BANGING ON DOOR)
-MAN: It's 9 o'clock, ladies!

13:32.720 --> 13:34.520
Open the fucking door!

13:36.840 --> 13:38.040
Fuck it.

13:38.920 --> 13:40.960
I'm not in the mood today.

13:44.320 --> 13:46.080
Let's go to the Bull Ring.

13:46.800 --> 13:48.200
Hallelujah!

13:48.280 --> 13:50.400
(ROCK MUSIC PLAYING)

14:25.440 --> 14:27.040
MICHAEL: The foolish man?

14:28.400 --> 14:29.720
Not quite.

14:48.960 --> 14:50.520
I'm sorry I came unannounced.

14:51.160 --> 14:52.200
What do you want?

14:52.800 --> 14:54.320
We need proof.

14:55.200 --> 14:57.280
Proof of what? (CLEARS THROAT)

14:57.360 --> 14:59.360
You said the priest is a traitor.

14:59.680 --> 15:01.280
We need to know how you know.

15:02.320 --> 15:03.680
The proof is my word.

15:05.600 --> 15:08.000
If he is involved, I'm out.
He needs to die.

15:08.600 --> 15:10.240
Are you always so violent?

15:13.200 --> 15:14.720
I killed a stag today,

15:15.680 --> 15:17.280
and it hurt me to do it.

15:18.560 --> 15:20.760
But I treated it with respect,

15:20.840 --> 15:23.120
and the spare meat
will go to poor people.

15:24.920 --> 15:28.840
It will grieve me far less
to put a bullet in the priest's face.

15:31.760 --> 15:34.000
Will you not sit when a duchess sits?

15:35.520 --> 15:38.040
I'm told you're part of the deal.
Is that true?

15:39.200 --> 15:42.360
The Royal Court in Tbilisi
actually worked very efficiently.

15:42.440 --> 15:45.120
Ah, I see. And it worked like this, eh?

15:45.200 --> 15:48.960
TATIANA: There were lots of
corridors and small rooms.

15:49.040 --> 15:50.280
Attics.

15:50.360 --> 15:52.720
There were no rules there.
Deals were done.

15:52.800 --> 15:54.760
Brothers gave sisters,
aunts gave uncles,

15:54.840 --> 15:56.600
fathers gave daughters and servants.

15:56.680 --> 15:57.840
(GLASS CLINKS)

15:59.480 --> 16:01.840
It was my aunt's idea that I came alone.

16:04.560 --> 16:06.360
She is in charge of this.

16:14.520 --> 16:17.320
When there are no rules,
women take charge.

16:18.000 --> 16:21.480
They understand that the power they have
comes through silent agreements.

16:21.560 --> 16:25.360
I've promised I will do everything I can
to make this plan work.

16:25.440 --> 16:28.320
My aunt assumed you would want me
as part of the deal.

16:30.240 --> 16:31.560
I will tell her she's wrong.

16:31.640 --> 16:33.800
-(FOOTSTEPS APPROACH)
-(DOOR OPENS)

16:34.400 --> 16:37.160
(CHUCKLING) Tommy,
you ain't gonna believe this, man.

16:37.680 --> 16:39.960
I just phoned the garrison, right?
I just spoke to Billy.

16:40.040 --> 16:44.640
He says Polly, Esme and Lizzie have
gone on fucking strike.

16:44.720 --> 16:46.000
(LAUGHS)

16:46.080 --> 16:48.320
-They what?
-They've gone on fucking strike!

16:49.160 --> 16:50.720
Half of Birmingham is out.

16:50.800 --> 16:53.680
The female half, they're all out,
every single one of them.

16:53.760 --> 16:55.040
Quakers put 'em up to it.

16:56.440 --> 16:57.600
Who's watching the shop?

16:58.160 --> 16:59.320
JOHN: Polly's locked it up.

17:00.120 --> 17:02.760
See, Good Friday's
one of our best days for takings.

17:04.200 --> 17:08.080
All the men get drunk.
The races are all fixed.

17:08.160 --> 17:11.120
It's like picking apples
off the lowest branches.

17:11.200 --> 17:12.480
Hey, John?

17:13.000 --> 17:14.080
Hmm, yes.

17:14.400 --> 17:16.120
Then your business is very easy.

17:18.360 --> 17:20.200
-Was Linda with them?
-You know,

17:20.800 --> 17:23.720
Billy said that Polly jumped
in the fucking Bull Ring,

17:23.800 --> 17:26.760
just pissed out of her mind,
started going on about revolution,

17:26.840 --> 17:28.080
screaming to the rooftops.

17:28.600 --> 17:30.320
Was Linda with them?

17:31.440 --> 17:32.560
Yeah.

17:33.400 --> 17:35.280
Then it was Linda's idea.

17:35.760 --> 17:38.480
-Linda's a smart woman.
-(FOOTSTEPS APPROACH)

17:44.800 --> 17:45.960
John.

17:47.120 --> 17:48.840
There's a Bentley in the drive outside.

17:48.920 --> 17:51.040
I want you to go out
and put a nail in its tyre.

17:51.120 --> 17:53.920
It's Good Friday,
so there'll be no garages open.

17:54.000 --> 17:55.600
The lady will have to spend the night.

17:56.040 --> 17:58.360
Then I want you and the boys
to all go home.

17:58.440 --> 18:01.040
You take Charlie, put him with
Arthur and Linda for the night.

18:01.120 --> 18:03.080
They can use the practise.

18:06.280 --> 18:08.200
-You want to put a nail...
-Yeah.

18:08.520 --> 18:10.160
-You heard me.
-Yeah.

18:10.560 --> 18:13.200
Right. Nice to meet you.

18:17.440 --> 18:19.840
Why do you need
to put a nail in the tyre?

18:20.560 --> 18:23.120
I want it so neither of us
can change our minds.

18:30.040 --> 18:31.360
(CREAKING)

18:33.320 --> 18:35.120
(CLANKING)

18:47.080 --> 18:48.680
JOHN: We came back early.

18:54.200 --> 18:56.080
Polly didn't finish the count yesterday.

18:56.920 --> 18:58.040
Hmm.

18:58.960 --> 19:00.560
So you thought you could take a tenner.

19:01.320 --> 19:02.920
I thought I'd finish the count.

19:07.400 --> 19:09.240
(BOTH GRUNTING)

19:10.680 --> 19:11.800
JOHN: Hey!

19:11.880 --> 19:14.480
Esme, I've told you.
Stay off the snow till the baby's born.

19:14.560 --> 19:17.520
ESME: It does no harm, passes the time.

19:17.600 --> 19:20.440
-Knocks down the walls.
-Listen. (GRUNTS)

19:21.600 --> 19:23.240
(PANTING) Listen.

19:24.440 --> 19:26.440
I know you miss the travelling.

19:27.160 --> 19:28.840
It's all gonna be all right.

19:29.800 --> 19:31.760
It's like being a hen in a coop.

19:35.840 --> 19:38.040
Remember that house in Lichfield?

19:39.160 --> 19:41.680
The one the bailiff used to
throw you out of?

19:41.760 --> 19:43.320
Throw you in the ditch.

19:44.920 --> 19:47.360
I'm gonna buy that fucking house.

19:48.040 --> 19:50.080
Big as Tommy's with more land.

19:51.400 --> 19:53.240
If you feel cooped up,

19:53.920 --> 19:58.000
we'll take a wagon,
camp out by the ditch.

19:59.440 --> 20:00.640
How?

20:03.000 --> 20:04.360
(SNIFFS)

20:05.080 --> 20:07.200
It's all gonna change, Esme.

20:13.120 --> 20:14.800
TATIANA: This is not your bedroom.

20:15.400 --> 20:17.840
This is not where
you slept with your wife.

20:18.600 --> 20:20.160
Do you ride horses?

20:20.640 --> 20:21.760
No.

20:21.840 --> 20:25.800
I would need to open my legs in
a public place and that is not allowed.

20:26.480 --> 20:27.640
You drink whisky?

20:28.160 --> 20:29.240
No.

20:29.760 --> 20:32.840
It tastes like men. I prefer wine.

20:34.680 --> 20:35.760
Cars?

20:36.360 --> 20:37.480
No.

20:38.120 --> 20:40.720
So, diamonds are your only love, eh?

20:40.800 --> 20:42.640
-Sapphires?
-(CHUCKLES)

20:44.160 --> 20:45.960
They're just a currency.

20:46.720 --> 20:50.200
Well, you know,
if it was me who had all them jewels,

20:52.760 --> 20:55.480
I think I'd just sit with them,

20:56.360 --> 20:57.600
look at them,

20:58.920 --> 20:59.960
touch them.

21:00.040 --> 21:01.640
Izabella does that sometimes.

21:02.080 --> 21:03.240
Late at night.

21:05.280 --> 21:08.680
I swear she puts one of the biggest
sapphires into her body for pleasure,

21:08.760 --> 21:11.560
and walks up the stairs
to breakfast with it still in place.

21:11.640 --> 21:12.880
(LAUGHS)

21:14.400 --> 21:16.640
-And it stays in there all day?
-Yeah.

21:16.720 --> 21:17.720
Oh.

21:18.880 --> 21:20.440
What is your weakness?

21:22.760 --> 21:25.360
Talking about duchesses
with sapphires inside of them.

21:25.440 --> 21:26.520
Mmm.

21:27.560 --> 21:29.680
I think I already know your weakness.

21:34.600 --> 21:36.520
I can get a fuck whenever I want, love.

21:36.920 --> 21:38.000
Yes.

21:39.280 --> 21:41.000
But I am a duchess.

21:42.520 --> 21:44.520
And I am under you like a horse.

21:44.600 --> 21:46.560
-I'm like a telegram.
-(CHUCKLING)

21:48.560 --> 21:51.000
"A telegram"?
I don't think your English is so good.

21:52.160 --> 21:53.960
Or maybe you should
listen more carefully

21:54.040 --> 21:55.600
to what I have to say.

21:56.680 --> 21:57.800
Hmm?

21:58.880 --> 22:01.120
I have a message for you, Mr Shelby.

22:03.080 --> 22:07.880
As a duchess, I can show you
what is possible for a man like you.

22:09.280 --> 22:12.240
A man in a house like this.

22:13.240 --> 22:17.000
Right now, you hide inside it like a boy
who's broken in through the window.

22:18.320 --> 22:21.200
Why did we come to a bedroom for this?
Hmm?

22:22.680 --> 22:23.880
In your own house?

22:29.400 --> 22:30.440
(DOOR OPENS)

22:32.520 --> 22:35.200
-(LAUGHS)
-That's a loaded fucking weapon.

22:35.280 --> 22:39.000
We could fuck by the fire with the maids
standing to attention and watching.

22:39.080 --> 22:40.120
What can they do?

22:40.200 --> 22:41.320
-Give it here.
-Nothing.

22:41.400 --> 22:43.840
There are no rules for you. Hmm?

22:43.920 --> 22:45.000
Give me the fucking gun.

22:45.080 --> 22:47.600
You have maids here.
You can bring a maid into the room.

22:47.680 --> 22:49.640
What can I do about that? Nothing.

22:49.720 --> 22:52.720
-Give me the fucking gun, now.
-You have power.

22:52.960 --> 22:55.720
Everyone does what you tell them to do.

22:55.800 --> 22:59.920
Your brothers, your soldiers,
no one can stop you.

23:00.000 --> 23:01.120
Don't point the fucking weapon at me.

23:01.200 --> 23:02.720
I can be an actress.

23:03.480 --> 23:05.080
Who do you want me to be?

23:06.080 --> 23:07.160
Your dead wife?

23:07.240 --> 23:08.800
Now, that's enough.
Give me the fucking gun!

23:08.880 --> 23:12.040
If you don't like something,
you say stop, and it stops. Hmm?

23:12.800 --> 23:14.560
But you are afraid of it.

23:14.640 --> 23:17.240
You break the law,
but you obey the rules. Why?

23:18.520 --> 23:21.280
Did you know that madness sets you free?

23:21.360 --> 23:23.760
Otherwise, we're just peasants
obeying the law.

23:26.160 --> 23:29.400
There is madness inside your head, too.
I can see that.

23:30.520 --> 23:32.520
Let a duchess show you something.

23:33.240 --> 23:34.680
(FOOTSTEPS THUDDING)

23:35.680 --> 23:36.760
(DOOR OPENS)

23:40.560 --> 23:41.960
(CLICKING)

23:44.160 --> 23:45.520
(GUN BARREL TURNS)

23:46.760 --> 23:49.200
I emptied the chamber,
except for one bullet.

23:49.280 --> 23:51.640
-No! No, please.
-This is a game we used to play.

23:52.360 --> 23:53.400
No.

23:54.120 --> 23:56.000
-Watch.
-Do not fucking do this.

23:56.080 --> 23:58.160
No. Look at me.

23:58.840 --> 23:59.880
Don't do this.

23:59.960 --> 24:01.000
-(CLICKS)
-No!

24:01.080 --> 24:02.960
Give me the fucking thing.

24:05.040 --> 24:07.360
It brings you alive. You won't try it?

24:07.440 --> 24:09.000
No, I do not want to try!

24:09.080 --> 24:12.160
And I do not want
your mad fucking Russian brains

24:12.240 --> 24:14.040
all over me fucking walls.

24:14.120 --> 24:15.880
I survive each time by the will of God.

24:15.960 --> 24:17.320
Get to fucking bed, now!

24:17.400 --> 24:19.200
TATIANA: I already called a maid.

24:19.280 --> 24:20.440
TOMMY: Fucking...

24:33.480 --> 24:34.600
You see?

24:35.560 --> 24:37.200
You are afraid.

24:39.400 --> 24:42.000
Like a boy who's broken in
through the window.

24:43.200 --> 24:45.840
I need to educate you
in how to run a house like this.

24:45.920 --> 24:47.160
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACH)

24:47.680 --> 24:49.120
Yes. Come down.

24:49.640 --> 24:50.680
Pour us a drink.

24:50.800 --> 24:52.880
Mary, go back to bed, please.

24:53.120 --> 24:55.840
You go back to bed, please.
This woman is drunk.

24:56.120 --> 24:57.880
That's all right, sir.
Should I pour whisky?

24:57.960 --> 25:00.440
-Yes, he will have whisky...
-No, go back to bed.

25:00.520 --> 25:02.600
He will have whisky
and I will have wine!

25:03.360 --> 25:04.680
Mary, go back to bed.

25:04.760 --> 25:06.480
-In a house like this...
-TOMMY: Stop talking.

25:06.560 --> 25:08.840
-The servants expect it.
-Go back to bed! Do as I say!

25:08.920 --> 25:10.560
Normally, if there's a call
after midnight,

25:10.640 --> 25:12.680
the maid who comes in
is the one in love with the master,

25:12.760 --> 25:16.600
-but she is not in love with you.
-This is not fucking Russia!

25:16.680 --> 25:19.520
(SOFTLY) Please, Mary.
Go back to bed, hey?

25:33.640 --> 25:35.680
I know your weakness, Tommy.

25:38.440 --> 25:39.880
It's freedom.

25:41.800 --> 25:43.040
Madness.

25:44.320 --> 25:45.640
Killing.

25:50.440 --> 25:55.280
I am the first one who understands you.

26:04.720 --> 26:06.280
(FOOTSTEPS THUDDING)

26:42.040 --> 26:43.800
I found her perfume.

26:45.280 --> 26:46.600
Put it on.

26:51.160 --> 26:54.320
What proof do you have
that the priest is a spy?

26:54.680 --> 26:57.080
I told you. I gave you my word.

27:15.440 --> 27:16.880
Then kill him.

27:19.920 --> 27:23.400
From now on, you must do
everything that you want to do.

27:52.520 --> 27:54.800
There'll be two of us for breakfast
this morning, Mary.

27:54.880 --> 27:57.320
She's gone for a walk by the river.

27:57.400 --> 27:59.960
-MARY: The lady left, sir.
-(CUTLERY CLINKS)

28:00.120 --> 28:01.840
Left? How?

28:02.480 --> 28:03.640
She took your car.

28:04.880 --> 28:05.920
She what?

28:06.000 --> 28:09.480
She was in a terrible hurry.
She said she had your permission.

28:10.000 --> 28:13.680
She told David to go to the garage
to get a new tyre for the Bentley.

28:13.760 --> 28:15.400
She said you could use that.

28:16.280 --> 28:18.440
And why the hell
would you listen to her, eh?

28:18.840 --> 28:20.400
The way she said it, sir.

28:53.920 --> 28:55.400
(DOOR CLOSES)

28:55.480 --> 28:58.200
-JOHN: How was she, Tom?
-Talkative, yeah.

28:58.280 --> 28:59.320
Hmm.

28:59.760 --> 29:01.440
I was fucking working, all right?

29:01.800 --> 29:02.840
Yeah.

29:04.720 --> 29:06.920
From what she said,
when she was out of her fucking mind,

29:07.000 --> 29:09.360
I'm pretty certain
the treasury is underneath the house.

29:09.440 --> 29:10.440
What have you got?

29:10.520 --> 29:12.800
Our Ada got this
from the British Library

29:12.880 --> 29:14.920
using her scholar's pass.

29:16.360 --> 29:17.640
She talks about her aunt

29:17.720 --> 29:19.640
coming up the stairs
to have her breakfast in the morning,

29:19.720 --> 29:22.680
which means
it has to be in the building somewhere.

29:22.760 --> 29:25.000
ARTHUR: Wine cellar. Septic.

29:25.480 --> 29:27.160
Kitchen cellar.

29:27.240 --> 29:28.440
And a tunnel under the river.

29:28.520 --> 29:29.960
They don't trust a soul in this country,

29:30.040 --> 29:33.680
so my guess is they've turned
one of the cellars into a strong room.

29:33.760 --> 29:34.840
Did you find someone, Arthur?

29:35.240 --> 29:36.640
Moss gave me this.

29:36.720 --> 29:38.840
Stefan Radischevsky.

29:38.920 --> 29:41.280
He's a kid from Greet,
lives in Cheltenham.

29:41.360 --> 29:45.080
Dad's a Russian. He has dreams of
owning a pub but he's got a record.

29:45.360 --> 29:47.000
-Breaking and entering.
-ARTHUR: Hmm.

29:47.080 --> 29:48.720
-And he speaks Russian?
-Yeah.

29:48.800 --> 29:51.760
Their butler drinks in a pub
called the Masons Arms.

29:51.840 --> 29:53.000
Get to him, tell him who we are,

29:53.080 --> 29:55.960
offer him some money
if he gives the kid a job in the house.

29:56.040 --> 29:57.360
-(KNOCKING ON DOOR)
-Wait.

29:57.920 --> 29:59.600
Talk to the kid,

29:59.680 --> 30:01.960
offer him one of the pubs
we took off the Italians

30:02.040 --> 30:05.280
if he works in the house for four weeks,
keeps his ears open.

30:05.360 --> 30:06.520
All right?

30:06.600 --> 30:07.760
Come.

30:10.080 --> 30:12.960
The executive committee of
the union of bookies and allied trades

30:13.040 --> 30:14.480
will see you now, sir.

30:24.240 --> 30:25.880
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

30:27.680 --> 30:31.040
I heard you were giving speeches
off the back of a wagon, Pol.

30:31.880 --> 30:34.600
I can't remember a fucking thing.

30:34.680 --> 30:38.000
Well, Moss tells me you were threatening
to burn down the town hall.

30:38.320 --> 30:40.800
Oh, Tommy, we were having a laugh.

30:42.120 --> 30:44.480
You know, actually,
the crowd around me was bigger

30:44.560 --> 30:46.240
than the crowd around Jessie Eden.

30:46.320 --> 30:47.520
TOMMY: Who's Jessie Eden?

30:47.600 --> 30:48.760
POLLY: She's too soft.

30:48.840 --> 30:50.760
You're not gonna
break the capitalist system

30:50.840 --> 30:53.520
talking about
separate lavatories for women.

30:53.600 --> 30:54.680
Who is Jessie Eden?

30:55.000 --> 30:56.400
She's our new best friend.

30:56.480 --> 30:58.480
Shop steward at the Lucas factory.

30:58.560 --> 31:00.440
A woman shop steward, I've heard of her.

31:00.520 --> 31:02.680
There is a leaflet here
if you want to take a look, Tommy.

31:04.840 --> 31:06.320
(LIZZIE CLEARS THROAT)

31:07.800 --> 31:10.800
So, a separate lavatory?
Is that it? Is that what you want?

31:11.440 --> 31:12.440
I don't know what you want.

31:12.520 --> 31:15.440
You have to tell me what it is
that you want and then I'll know.

31:15.840 --> 31:19.720
Actually, we want to know
about the robbery you're planning.

31:19.800 --> 31:22.160
Not the factory robbery. The other one.

31:22.800 --> 31:25.040
The one you're not
telling the women about.

31:25.480 --> 31:27.200
-John has a big mouth.
-ESME: No.

31:28.400 --> 31:33.040
Arthur's got a big mouth.
Arthur told Linda, Linda told me.

31:34.800 --> 31:36.400
-Polly?
-Read the leaflet, Tommy.

31:36.480 --> 31:39.360
Ladies, why don't I
talk to Tommy privately,

31:39.440 --> 31:41.680
and then I'll
report back to you faithfully.

31:41.760 --> 31:44.400
You're not just gonna take payment
from the Russians, are you, Tommy?

31:44.800 --> 31:46.800
You're going to clean them out,
is that right?

31:46.880 --> 31:47.960
-LIZZIE: Esme?
-So...

31:48.600 --> 31:51.360
What happens after,
when they come for us?

31:51.440 --> 31:52.840
When I'm about to give birth?

31:52.920 --> 31:55.520
Get out, get back to work.

31:55.600 --> 31:56.800
Esme, come on.

31:59.400 --> 32:02.000
-Keep us posted, won't you, sister?
-I will.

32:03.200 --> 32:04.200
(DOOR CLOSES)

32:06.840 --> 32:07.920
Fucking hell.

32:11.720 --> 32:13.800
So Arthur tells Linda everything, eh?

32:14.240 --> 32:17.360
She's stolen his soul
and taken it to a better place.

32:17.440 --> 32:18.480
The suburbs.

32:18.880 --> 32:21.000
Where men are honest with their wives.

32:22.360 --> 32:23.360
We can trust Lizzie.

32:24.840 --> 32:26.840
Yeah, but I can't trust Esme.

32:27.440 --> 32:29.720
I can't trust the fucking Russians
to pay me or the army,

32:29.800 --> 32:32.560
and I can't trust my own brother
to keep his fucking mouth shut.

32:33.800 --> 32:35.520
Did you make progress last night?

32:39.000 --> 32:40.120
Yes.

32:41.960 --> 32:45.440
John said the girl looks like
Edna Purviance from the pictures.

32:45.960 --> 32:47.840
(CLICKS TONGUE) Be careful.

32:50.880 --> 32:52.640
She's an excellent source of information

32:52.720 --> 32:54.280
regarding the location
of the merchandise.

32:54.360 --> 32:55.360
-Here we go.
-You know,

32:55.440 --> 32:58.440
there is a general lack of discipline
in this fucking company.

33:00.280 --> 33:02.000
She stayed the night.

33:03.400 --> 33:04.800
I'm working, Pol.

33:05.440 --> 33:07.880
I am working for
the good of the company.

33:10.160 --> 33:11.400
You're grieving.

33:12.840 --> 33:14.560
And when you grieve,
you make bad choices.

33:15.120 --> 33:17.880
I know. I did it myself.

33:17.960 --> 33:20.000
Look. No more marches.

33:20.760 --> 33:22.240
No more fucking politics.

33:22.320 --> 33:24.720
It can kill us. All right?
Joke or no joke.

33:25.320 --> 33:26.880
Did you tell Arthur about the priest?

33:27.440 --> 33:28.840
I only told you.

33:30.120 --> 33:31.480
Thanks for the burden.

33:33.920 --> 33:35.280
(BELL TOLLING)

33:43.320 --> 33:45.800
You were correct
not to talk over the phone.

33:45.880 --> 33:47.520
What did she say?

33:49.680 --> 33:52.880
She said there was gonna be a killing.
A holy man.

33:54.640 --> 33:57.000
And she was with the Shelbys, was she?

33:57.800 --> 33:59.000
(SIGHS)

34:27.200 --> 34:29.880
I suppose you have something to say
about yesterday.

34:30.520 --> 34:31.760
No.

34:31.840 --> 34:33.480
It's something else, actually.

34:37.200 --> 34:38.440
I believe Arthur has told you

34:38.520 --> 34:40.920
about some business
we're planning, Linda.

34:41.400 --> 34:43.400
Oh, there's always business, Thomas.

34:43.760 --> 34:45.800
And Arthur believes when
this business is done,

34:45.880 --> 34:47.160
it'll all be over.

34:48.560 --> 34:50.800
Arthur believes you, but I don't.

34:52.600 --> 34:53.640
(SIGHS)

34:53.720 --> 34:58.400
Linda, the people who have hired us
to rob the factory are very bad people.

34:59.320 --> 35:01.040
They'll not pay us, as they've promised.

35:01.120 --> 35:05.240
So, on the night of the robbery, we will
take what is ours from their treasury.

35:05.320 --> 35:06.960
And a bit more on top for luck.

35:07.240 --> 35:09.560
If you're saying
you're gonna stop Arthur,

35:09.640 --> 35:10.880
I need to know.

35:11.600 --> 35:13.200
That'll be Arthur's decision.

35:14.440 --> 35:16.760
And your plan is still
to reform him, eh?

35:16.840 --> 35:19.760
-To the absolute degree of redemption.
-Mmm-hmm.

35:21.400 --> 35:25.320
Well, Arthur will walk away from this
with £30,000. We made a deal.

35:25.560 --> 35:26.920
And afterwards,

35:28.000 --> 35:30.680
you and Arthur can begin your new life.

35:35.320 --> 35:37.040
Did you say 30,000?

35:38.200 --> 35:41.520
Arthur said the estimated total proceeds
would be 150,000.

35:41.600 --> 35:43.920
-Estimated. Yes.
-A third of 150 is 50.

35:44.000 --> 35:45.360
-Why a third?
-The three brothers.

35:45.440 --> 35:47.000
-Finn is not yet a man.
-There are expenses.

35:47.080 --> 35:48.400
Of 25,000, you said.

35:48.560 --> 35:50.400
As of last night,
the expenses increased.

35:50.480 --> 35:51.840
We need to dig a hole.

35:51.920 --> 35:53.920
Arthur agreed to a plan
with a figure of 25.

35:55.520 --> 35:58.200
25 from 150 is 125.

35:58.280 --> 36:01.360
A third of that is £41,000.

36:02.880 --> 36:04.000
(SCOFFS)

36:05.360 --> 36:06.440
Sugar?

36:07.080 --> 36:08.080
Yes.

36:11.120 --> 36:12.880
(CROCKERY CLINKING)

36:14.440 --> 36:15.760
Thank you.

36:17.560 --> 36:19.200
(TOMMY CLEARS THROAT)

36:23.520 --> 36:26.040
So, you've worked this all out, I see?

36:26.640 --> 36:29.240
Only in my head.
I haven't written it down.

36:31.040 --> 36:33.240
Linda, are you saying...

36:35.920 --> 36:37.680
If it were 41,000...

36:37.760 --> 36:41.240
I've already told you,
that'll be Arthur's decision.

36:42.600 --> 36:45.360
But I don't imagine
he'll accept less than 41.

36:48.520 --> 36:50.240
-May I smoke?
-No.

36:57.520 --> 36:59.240
So, I imagine you have some plans

37:00.800 --> 37:02.280
for your 41,000.

37:03.320 --> 37:05.640
Yes. California.

37:06.400 --> 37:08.640
For the child's health,
away from the smoke.

37:09.160 --> 37:11.720
We want to run a general store
on an Indian mission.

37:12.360 --> 37:15.480
The Americans invite Quakers
to do good work with the Indians.

37:16.720 --> 37:19.040
We've already sent our papers
and been accepted.

37:20.320 --> 37:21.760
(CHUCKLES)

37:21.840 --> 37:23.880
Arthur Shelby as a missionary...

37:23.960 --> 37:27.280
-No. Arthur will run the store.
-Hmm.

37:28.000 --> 37:29.880
I will teach in the school next to it.

37:31.040 --> 37:34.840
Arthur will swim in the ocean.
I will be on the beach with a towel.

37:34.920 --> 37:35.960
The open air and the sun

37:36.040 --> 37:38.360
will get rid of all the nonsense
in his head from France.

37:42.280 --> 37:43.760
That's some plan.

37:44.680 --> 37:46.240
As you know yourself,

37:47.680 --> 37:48.680
the arrival of a new life

37:48.760 --> 37:51.160
concentrates the mind
on practical things.

37:51.640 --> 37:53.080
Amen to that.

37:56.520 --> 37:57.720
When is the child due?

37:58.000 --> 37:59.240
September.

37:59.800 --> 38:00.920
When is the robbery?

38:02.160 --> 38:03.280
June.

38:04.880 --> 38:06.760
Then the timing's perfect.

38:08.760 --> 38:10.440
We'll book a passage
through the Panama Canal

38:10.520 --> 38:13.400
the day after
the 41,000 is paid to Arthur.

38:13.480 --> 38:14.680
(COUGHING)

38:16.280 --> 38:18.640
Did we agree 41,000, Linda?

38:19.600 --> 38:21.240
I heard nothing to the contrary.

38:24.080 --> 38:27.040
-RUBEN: Word association. Right now.
-Oh, God. I hate this game.

38:27.120 --> 38:28.560
It's Freud. It's terribly fashionable.

38:28.640 --> 38:31.200
I'd rather you put on
that music that I hate.

38:31.280 --> 38:33.880
(SIGHS) Are we going mad
in here, do you think?

38:33.960 --> 38:35.000
Yes.

38:35.240 --> 38:37.880
(CHUCKLES) We shouldn't have drunk
red wine with the cake.

38:38.360 --> 38:42.160
And I believe your vow never to sleep
with another man is a good one.

38:42.800 --> 38:44.080
Good for the painting.

38:45.120 --> 38:47.080
It's not a vow. It's just...

38:48.280 --> 38:51.720
I think when men want sex,
they become hilarious.

38:52.840 --> 38:57.480
Like a dog, when you pick up a lead,
and he knows he's going for a walk.

39:02.480 --> 39:04.800
May I respectfully point out

39:05.200 --> 39:09.680
that so far you haven't even
picked up the bloody lead.

39:14.960 --> 39:16.000
There.

39:18.880 --> 39:20.040
That's the look.

39:20.720 --> 39:21.920
Imperious.

39:23.600 --> 39:26.080
No man is good enough.

39:46.280 --> 39:48.360
(CHILDREN CHATTERING)

39:51.680 --> 39:53.600
-(ROARS)
-(ALL SCREAMING)

39:57.360 --> 39:58.960
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

40:34.760 --> 40:36.440
(WATER DRIPPING)

41:01.880 --> 41:03.320
(GRUNTING)

41:32.800 --> 41:34.280
(BOTH GRUNTING)

41:36.480 --> 41:38.080
(SCREAMING)

41:40.240 --> 41:41.400
(CRACK)

41:42.800 --> 41:43.800
(THUD)

41:46.840 --> 41:48.320
(ENGINE IDLING)

42:05.600 --> 42:07.280
(INHALES SHARPLY)

42:30.440 --> 42:32.920
PATRICK: You idiot.
You nearly killed him.

42:33.000 --> 42:35.480
I told you we needed him
fully conscious.

42:36.160 --> 42:39.880
We need to stop using soldiers
who've been in India, they hit too hard.

42:39.960 --> 42:41.440
HUGHES: Not fucking hard enough.

42:41.520 --> 42:43.320
Hey, Mr Shelby. Hey.

42:43.400 --> 42:46.240
I heard about your plan
to kill a holy man

42:46.320 --> 42:48.560
from a voice in the confessional.

42:48.640 --> 42:49.800
PATRICK: Can you hear us?

42:49.880 --> 42:51.080
(GROANS)

42:51.280 --> 42:52.320
Grace?

42:52.760 --> 42:53.960
Shelby.

42:55.600 --> 42:57.880
Why were you attempting
to kill Father Hughes?

43:00.040 --> 43:02.680
Maybe we should wait
until he is fully conscious.

43:02.760 --> 43:04.400
I have a dinner appointment.

43:05.080 --> 43:06.800
Hey, Shelby?

43:07.200 --> 43:09.000
Wake up. Eyes front.

43:09.080 --> 43:10.200
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

43:10.280 --> 43:12.920
Mr Shelby, you were trying to kill me,
were you?

43:14.840 --> 43:16.280
Passing information...

43:17.080 --> 43:18.920
PATRICK: Fuck. He knows.

43:24.160 --> 43:25.320
Where am I?

43:26.080 --> 43:30.160
You are among the Odd Fellows.
Please count from 10 to one.

43:30.640 --> 43:31.960
Ah, fuck you.

43:54.840 --> 43:59.200
Whatever else you might have forgotten
about last night,

43:59.960 --> 44:01.080
remember this.

44:02.520 --> 44:05.320
I am passing on information
to the Soviet Embassy

44:05.840 --> 44:07.560
on the instruction of Section D.

44:08.760 --> 44:10.960
It's part of a bigger picture.

44:11.400 --> 44:15.800
You explain to the Russians
that you were mistaken about me,

44:16.080 --> 44:18.920
and you apologise to me
in front of them.

44:22.000 --> 44:24.840
A threat on your sister
was evidently not enough.

44:25.280 --> 44:28.800
You do as we say,
or we will take your son.

44:29.760 --> 44:33.360
Hear this. We will take your son.

44:33.960 --> 44:35.800
We can do it at any moment.

44:36.400 --> 44:38.880
We have people in your life.

44:43.000 --> 44:46.120
You will make your apology to me
tomorrow night,

44:47.520 --> 44:50.160
and you will repair the damage
you've done.

44:51.040 --> 44:53.520
(ECHOING) Or you will never
see your son again.

45:06.120 --> 45:07.320
(GROANING)

45:19.400 --> 45:20.880
(DOOR OPENS)

45:20.960 --> 45:22.600
MARY: Sir, I don't understand...

45:22.680 --> 45:24.400
(TOMMY PANTING)

45:24.480 --> 45:27.880
I don't understand why,
as a former soldier yourself,

45:27.960 --> 45:30.720
you have sacked all of the former
soldiers on the staff.

45:30.800 --> 45:32.800
It means there is only one man
left in the household.

45:32.880 --> 45:35.840
Mary, I want it so that
Charles is never left on his own.

45:35.920 --> 45:37.000
Understood?

45:38.120 --> 45:39.960
Sir, I should call a doctor.

45:40.040 --> 45:42.600
There will be some men
coming down from Birmingham.

45:42.960 --> 45:44.560
And you put them up here in the house.

45:44.640 --> 45:47.440
You put them in the front and back of
the house, you feed them, and you...

45:47.560 --> 45:49.480
Why are they needed, sir?

45:49.560 --> 45:52.480
I brought a cursed sapphire
into this house, Mary.

45:53.160 --> 45:54.840
And now, I'm paying for it.

45:57.600 --> 45:59.600
And I don't know what to expect.

46:00.600 --> 46:02.640
But neither do my enemies.

46:03.160 --> 46:05.840
Tell David to bring the car around.
I'm going to go to London.

46:06.200 --> 46:08.760
-Sir...
-And get me some tea, Mary.

46:11.280 --> 46:12.560
Yes, sir.

46:13.720 --> 46:14.720
(DOOR OPENS)

46:36.880 --> 46:37.920
ARTHUR: (ON PHONE) <i>Hello?</i>

46:38.000 --> 46:39.600
-Yes, Arthur.
<i>-Tommy?</i>

46:41.160 --> 46:44.640
They want the robbery to be sabotaged.

46:45.160 --> 46:46.880
They don't give a fuck who gets hurt.

46:46.960 --> 46:48.000
<i>Are you OK, Tommy?</i>

46:48.080 --> 46:50.080
-It's a bigger picture now.
<i>.What...</i>

46:50.920 --> 46:52.080
Did John make a list?

46:52.160 --> 46:53.640
<i>Speak clearer, Tom.</i>

46:53.720 --> 46:54.960
I said did John make a list?

46:55.040 --> 46:57.040
<i>John.Boy! John!</i>

46:57.120 --> 46:58.200
Right.

46:58.520 --> 47:01.800
<i>Gypsies and kin only. Yeah.</i>

47:01.880 --> 47:03.040
Good.

47:03.800 --> 47:06.000
<i>Tommy, can task you why?</i>

47:06.080 --> 47:07.160
<i>Tommy?</i>

47:09.640 --> 47:11.160
(PHONE RINGING)

47:11.240 --> 47:13.960
ADA: No, Karl. I told you.
Go on and play in there.

47:17.400 --> 47:18.440
Hello?

47:19.920 --> 47:23.800
(SIGHS) Ada, it's me. It's Tommy.

47:25.200 --> 47:26.600
Ada, I need you to...

47:27.360 --> 47:30.160
I need you to speak
to one of your comrades

47:30.240 --> 47:33.640
and get me a meeting
with someone from the Soviet Embassy.

47:34.920 --> 47:36.160
Tonight.

47:36.480 --> 47:38.480
Your place, 10 p.m.

47:43.480 --> 47:44.960
(RETCHING)

47:47.880 --> 47:50.120
It seems that Mr Shelby

47:50.200 --> 47:52.640
was given bad information
by an informant

47:53.120 --> 47:55.560
who was also in contact
with the underwriter,

47:56.760 --> 48:00.040
who, as we know,
is in the pocket of the Soviets.

48:01.800 --> 48:04.240
-Wine, Tatiana?
-A little.

48:06.960 --> 48:08.280
Bad girl.

48:11.880 --> 48:13.520
(SNIFFING)

48:29.920 --> 48:31.360
(DOOR OPENS)

48:35.040 --> 48:36.200
(DOOR CLOSES)

48:39.280 --> 48:40.720
(SNIFFS)

48:40.800 --> 48:42.600
Sorry I'm late. I, uh...

48:45.720 --> 48:48.600
There was a body on the line.
(CLEARS THROAT)

48:49.000 --> 48:50.280
Drink, Mr Shelby?

48:51.200 --> 48:52.400
No, thank you.

48:52.480 --> 48:54.160
It was drink that caused
half this trouble.

48:55.200 --> 48:57.760
I have come here to apologise.

48:59.120 --> 49:01.640
I have already explained
that you now realise

49:01.720 --> 49:06.280
that your absurd allegation against me
was false.

49:07.160 --> 49:08.320
Indeed.

49:08.720 --> 49:11.640
HUGHES: And that your base nature
made you rash.

49:12.040 --> 49:13.240
(SNIFFS)

49:14.200 --> 49:17.680
And that now, once again,
our plan is back on track.

49:19.080 --> 49:22.040
When a child in my care commits a sin,

49:23.560 --> 49:26.440
first of all, he confesses,
as you just did.

49:26.920 --> 49:29.800
And then,
I instruct him to perform penance

49:30.480 --> 49:32.400
in a manner of my choosing.

49:32.880 --> 49:34.480
As a child, you went to church?

49:35.120 --> 49:36.200
Yes.

49:36.680 --> 49:38.640
HUGHES: Do you remember
the Act of Contrition?

49:40.480 --> 49:41.760
Good.

49:41.840 --> 49:43.680
Do you remember
the words of the Act of Contrition?

49:45.520 --> 49:46.720
(CLEARS THROAT) Yes.

49:49.320 --> 49:52.440
As your penance,
I would like you to recite it now,

49:53.560 --> 49:55.560
in the presence of our associates.

49:57.480 --> 49:58.680
(DOOR OPENS)

50:00.960 --> 50:02.280
Go away.

50:04.360 --> 50:05.680
(TOMMY CLEARS THROAT)

50:06.640 --> 50:07.640
(DOOR CLOSES)

50:08.280 --> 50:09.480
Uh...

50:14.000 --> 50:17.320
Oh, my God,
I am heartily sorry for having...

50:17.400 --> 50:19.600
HUGHES: Instead of "God," say my name.

50:20.360 --> 50:23.320
Since it was me you offended
with your false allegation.

50:27.200 --> 50:30.680
Father Hughes, I am heartily sorry
for having offended you,

50:34.280 --> 50:35.560
because of your just punishment,

50:35.640 --> 50:37.480
but most of all,
because they offend you.

50:40.320 --> 50:44.080
Father Hughes, who art all good
and deserving of my love,

50:44.800 --> 50:45.920
(SIGHS)

50:46.920 --> 50:48.520
I firmly resolve to...

50:50.960 --> 50:53.200
With the help of your grace,
to sin no more

50:53.280 --> 50:56.280
and to avoid all near occasions of sin.

50:57.560 --> 50:58.640
Mmm.

51:01.360 --> 51:04.120
Very good. Thank you.

51:05.160 --> 51:06.320
Amen.

51:09.640 --> 51:10.720
(SIGHS)

51:13.080 --> 51:17.160
And now that we are
a united band once more,

51:17.240 --> 51:19.160
perhaps we could order some food.

51:20.400 --> 51:23.240
I'm sorry. I am not feeling well.
I have to go. Good night.

51:24.800 --> 51:26.120
Mr Shelby...

51:32.840 --> 51:34.120
(SNIFFING)

51:35.080 --> 51:36.080
My God, Tommy.

51:36.160 --> 51:37.200
-Are they here?
-Yeah.

51:37.640 --> 51:39.680
-Do you have cocaine?
-No.

51:39.760 --> 51:41.440
-(SIGHS)
-Tommy.

51:44.440 --> 51:47.200
Tommy, this is the Special Adviser
to the Soviet Consul.

51:55.360 --> 51:59.560
Members of the British establishment
and exiled White Russians

51:59.640 --> 52:03.480
are planning to rob armoured cars
from a factory in Birmingham.

52:03.600 --> 52:06.120
We know about the robbery.
We have an informant.

52:06.200 --> 52:10.200
No, your informant is working for them.
They want you to know about the robbery.

52:11.840 --> 52:12.920
(SPEAKING RUSSIAN)

52:17.960 --> 52:20.560
Your informant
is working to their instruction.

52:21.840 --> 52:23.160
(SPEAKING RUSSIAN)

52:27.000 --> 52:28.920
Why would they want us to know?

52:29.000 --> 52:30.320
They want you to...

52:31.160 --> 52:33.160
They want you to stop the robbery.

52:33.240 --> 52:36.560
They want you to commit a violent act
on British soil.

52:36.640 --> 52:37.800
Tommy, do you want water?

52:38.240 --> 52:39.680
A violent act on British...

52:40.840 --> 52:42.040
(DIMITRI SPEAKING RUSSIAN)

52:44.160 --> 52:45.320
(SIGHS)

52:46.720 --> 52:50.200
To force the British government
to break off diplomatic relations.

52:50.520 --> 52:52.040
(DIMITRI SPEAKING RUSSIAN)

52:54.360 --> 52:56.040
(SNIFFS) That's the game.

52:57.560 --> 52:59.440
The robbery in Birmingham
is just the bait.

52:59.880 --> 53:01.280
(DIMITRI SPEAKING RUSSIAN)

53:03.920 --> 53:05.760
Why are you telling us this?

53:06.600 --> 53:09.240
Because my family are the ones
who will be sacrificed

53:10.280 --> 53:12.120
if you decide to blow up the train.

53:12.520 --> 53:13.760
(DIMITRI SPEAKING RUSSIAN)

53:18.760 --> 53:21.200
The Consul wants to know who you are.

53:22.440 --> 53:23.720
He's Tommy Shelby.

53:24.080 --> 53:25.960
You can take his word.

53:26.040 --> 53:27.600
-Ada.
-Tommy...

53:27.680 --> 53:28.800
Ada.

53:29.200 --> 53:30.280
OK.

53:30.600 --> 53:32.160
(ADA GRUNTING)

53:36.120 --> 53:37.560
Stop, stop.

53:37.640 --> 53:39.440
Ada, stop.

53:39.800 --> 53:41.880
(GRUNTS) OK.

53:44.800 --> 53:46.360
Drive me to a hospital, Ada.

53:47.640 --> 53:51.240
If I'm not conscious when I get there,
tell them I have a fractured skull,

53:51.320 --> 53:52.960
concussion and internal bleeding.

53:53.440 --> 53:54.880
I think I may have haemorrhaged.

53:54.960 --> 53:56.320
-Tommy.
-Ada, go on.

53:56.400 --> 53:57.720
-Be quick because I can't see.
-OK.

53:57.800 --> 53:59.200
I can't fucking see.

54:00.280 --> 54:01.960
(SOBS) OK. OK.

54:10.320 --> 54:12.080
Except for you, Dad.

54:16.960 --> 54:18.440
I can see you.

54:36.520 --> 54:38.520
(THEME SONG PLAYING)

54:38.544 --> 54:43.544
http://hiqve.com/
